      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Svetozar Botorić with a beard. He has thinning hair. He is wearing a white shirt with a banded collar, a dark bow tie and a dark jacket.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Studio portrait. Botorić was the owner of Belgrade’s first permanent cinema ‘Pariz’, established in 1908, and producer of three out of four feature films produced in Serbia before World War I.</ab>
